Great service if you want the owner to give you Covid. Doesn’t keep his mask on and you can hear him spewing his politics all around. 1/5 stars. We have a newborn at home and we’re hoping to go somewhere and stay safe. The other staff was very safe and welcoming. Kept their mask on and talked about normal life not QAnon conspiracy theories!

We had my daughter’s wedding ceremony and reception in the Penthouse recently. The room is beautiful with great atmosphere. The food was delicious and plentiful. The staff were very friendly and helpful and the service was superb. I would highly recommend O’Sheas. They helped to make the night perfect!!
Nice place and friendly people

We had our down-sized wedding due to Covid at The Penthouse at Oshea’s this past Saturday and amazing/outstanding is an understatement. Service was awesome and the servers/bartenders were always checking up on how we were and if we needed more drinks/anything they could do to help. The food was delicious and the atmosphere was amazing. We had such a fun time on the dance floor and would recommend booking osheas for any kind of wedding reception. The venue is stunning and beautiful, I wish we could relive that night already!!! Love love love.

Wonderful atmosphere and amazing food! The fries had the perfect Cajun flavor. The peanut butter milkshake was totally worth the extra calories. Jess was so kind and awesome!

nice place to relax, people watch, eat good, etc.  next time i'll be back with my coworkers. this place has an awesome atmosphere. they have so many great reviews for a reason.

Landon made sure we had an amazing time while we were there and was awesome at making us feel welcome. Will definitely be back and recommend to anyone in the area.

I was in town for a wedding and stopped by.  The drinks were reasonably priced and they had the best homemade sauces I've ever tasted for their chicken fingers (which are cut fresh and not frozen out of a bag like most pubs).  I complimented the bartender on how good they were and he gave me some free sauces to go.  Definitely recommended.
Good food

Awesome atmosphere, diverse clientele.  High velocity customer service,  great food and beer,  and the staff's obvious enthusiasm for working there made this the highlight of our most recent visit to Louisville .  Planned to start there and move on, but our party of four were happy to stay and soak up a terrific Saturday evening!

I'll have to come back and try this again, I know they're doing the best they can with virus bs happening, but it was just a pretty lousy experience. I have a feeling though before the wuhuflu this place was hopping. Will come again and try it again.

When our meals came, the server never returned to check on us, refill any drinks, etc.  My wife really enjoyed the shrimp and grits.  I had the beer battered fish and chips.  The cod was excellent, but the batter was a bit thick and too greasy for my taste.  My daughter had the reuben.  The bottom of the sandwich was very soggy and unappetizing.

We recently hosted our wedding and reception at O'Shea's and it was a wonderful experience. Our guests could not stop talking about the service and food. It was absolutely top notch. They also could not stop raving about how pretty of a venue. We would totally recommend Patrick O'Shea's to others if they are looking for a beautiful/unique venue with great food and service!

Came to a private event with Wen. The bar staff on the event was amazing. What made me and three others upset was the ‘manager’ on duty. She came to check on the event with a drink in her hand being VERY loud. Her entitlement with the company was upsetting. We all came to have a great night and she kind of ruined it. She, later found out her name was Jessica, seemed intoxicated and unprofessional with her staff. Jessica looked unprofessional with her faded dyed hair. She shoved one of my colleagues while stumbling to the bar to address the bartenders. Very unprofessional and put most of us on edge. Interrupting a great night which we as a company spent plenty of time planning. Happy ‘Oaks day’. Guess you can’t keep the drunks out of the bar.

I love Patrick O'shea's!! Even when you guys are packed and seem to only have a few people working, service and food is on point. I don't know of any other late night food spots that are anywhere near as great. On weeknights, you can get food from the regular menu til 11pm and may be even later on the weekends and they even have a shortened late night menu for after 11 til i think 12 or 1am. I absolutely love this place.  Tonight around 10pm we got carryout and i asked for the salmon and to sub out my side of greens for carrots and celery.. I was expecting them to throw a few raw carrot sliced in my box (like they use for the wings with celery sticks) since carrots arent really on the menu. They actually cooked me some carrots to perfection which was an unexpected treat. They eaily could have just tossed in raw carrot slices but someone in their kitchen took the time to do that and i really appreciated that.  Can't say enough how grateful i am to have such a good late night food spot. Thanks again for always being awesome. My only wish is that the salmon came with a little sauce because it was a tad on the dry side but i still really enjoyed it.
Kevin is the best bartender!! I have a special needs little brother, Kevin is so friendly and makes him feel so special he wants to sit at the bar every time we go now!

We walked in on a Friday evening thinking the place would be packed. Surprisingly, we were able to seat ourselves immediately. We didn't know what to expect, but the menu looked decent. I ordered the guacamole and pita which turned out to be incredibly delicious; our whole table enjoyed it. The fish and chips were very tasty; they were fried perfectly and the tartar sauce was delicious. My table also greatly enjoyed the reuben and collard greens. The fries and tater tots were so-so- they weren't hot and the texture left more to be desired. Otherwise, we had a great experience- good food, friendly and prompt service, and all in the great city of Louisville! I would definitely recommend Patrick O'Shea's! Thanks for the food and memories!
Comfortable atmosphere, tasty food, good service. Our favorite place to get a drink along whiskey row when in Louisville.
